  "title": "OcularLDT",
  "description": "OcularLDT is a neuroimaging dataset containing eye-tracking and neural recordings acquired during a lexical decision task with ocular components. The dataset includes multimodal data designed to investigate the relationship between eye movements and neural activity during language processing, providing a resource for studying the neural correlates of visual word recognition and oculomotor control.",
